WEBVTT

00:10.656 --> 00:14.980
Someone's saying there
wasn't anywhere to run.

00:14.981 --> 00:16.647
Serial killer pops in my head.

00:16.648 --> 00:19.557
I said, if you're here,
open this door now.

00:19.558 --> 00:22.166
I don't like it. I just
want to be out of here.

00:22.167 --> 00:24.487
He wound up murdering his own mother.

00:24.488 --> 00:26.797
- And how'd he do that?
- With an ax.

00:26.798 --> 00:30.458
Oh, [Bleep] It's time for me
to live here with my family.

00:30.459 --> 00:33.543
This guy is saying,
make sure they're dead.

00:33.544 --> 00:36.604
Make sure. Make sure.

00:37.992 --> 00:39.599
It's really bad in here.

00:39.600 --> 00:42.518
My name is Amy Allan.

00:42.519 --> 00:44.499
Something is not right.

00:44.500 --> 00:45.662
I see dead people.

00:45.663 --> 00:47.903
This person might have
been a serial killer.

00:47.904 --> 00:49.739
I speak to dead people.

00:49.740 --> 00:51.542
You get those chills.

00:51.543 --> 00:52.943
And they speak to me.

00:52.944 --> 00:55.412
He is darkness. He is evil.

00:55.413 --> 00:58.381
But there's only one way to
know if my findings are real.

00:58.382 --> 00:59.954
I think she broke her neck.

00:59.955 --> 01:01.184
I rely on my partner.

01:01.185 --> 01:05.254
I'm Steve Di Schiavi. I'm a retired
New York City homicide Detective.

01:05.254 --> 01:07.256
You telling me the truth?

01:07.257 --> 01:10.391
And I know every person,
every house has secrets.

01:10.392 --> 01:11.992
I think the Devil is down here.

01:11.993 --> 01:13.494
It's my job to reveal them.

01:13.495 --> 01:14.842
Who the hell would do this?

01:14.843 --> 01:17.097
But Steve and I never speak...

01:17.098 --> 01:19.065
We never communicate
during an investigation.

01:19.066 --> 01:20.433
Until the very end.

01:20.434 --> 01:21.800
Who is he looking to kill?

01:21.801 --> 01:23.769
We uncover if it's
safe for you to stay...

01:23.770 --> 01:26.071
You need to get out of here right now.

01:26.072 --> 01:27.239
Or time to get out.

01:27.240 --> 01:30.840
It was like endless darkness.

